- In the dns directory there's an example of how to write a DNS client
using  ares  and RTL-lwIP.   

- In the raw_api  directory there's an example  of how to use the  raw
API.

- In the sequential_api directory there  are some examples showing how
to use the sequential  API. Particulary, the  tcpclient example in the
tcp_echo   subdirectory  also shows   how  to use  sys_thread_register
despite of sys_thread_new.

- In the sockets_api directory you'll find a TCP echo client using the
sockets API.


RTL-lwIP home page:

http://rtl-lwip.sourceforge.net

Please send comments to Sergio Perez <serpeal@upvnet.upv.es>
